00:41.857 --> 00:46.275
The Specialist (1994)

01:09.486 --> 01:10.652
Nice view.

02:00.870 --> 02:02.955
Perfect timing.

02:15.009 --> 02:17.177
Wait a minute. He's not alone.

02:17.345 --> 02:19.388
That's a heartbreaking piece of news.

02:19.556 --> 02:21.640
Pull the plug, Ned.
There's a kid in the car.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.559
There's a drug lord in the car, Ray.

02:23.852 --> 02:26.770
- Kid just took a bad ride, that's all.
- Abort the action.

02:26.938 --> 02:29.898
You're the rigger.
I am the trigger. I make the call.

02:30.066 --> 02:34.278
You just sit back and watch the show.
Okay, sport?

02:35.738 --> 02:37.948
Activate the fail-safe,
you fucking psycho.

02:38.658 --> 02:41.285
Here's a tip, Ray. There is no fail-safe.

02:41.911 --> 02:43.495
Come on. Come on.

03:06.102 --> 03:07.352
You'll never make it.

04:15.964 --> 04:18.339
You're an arrogant man, Raymond.

04:18.507 --> 04:21.969
I taught you everything you know
and you dare to turn on me.

04:22.136 --> 04:23.762
Are you gonna kill me too, colonel?

04:23.930 --> 04:26.890
You're a specialist, captain.
You deserve better.

04:39.237 --> 04:41.029
Don't forget to write, partner.

05:06.889 --> 05:09.599
You like watching her die?
You like taking them down?

05:09.767 --> 05:13.520
Now I'm taking you down.
You're finished in the agency.

05:14.230 --> 05:15.897
You're going nowhere.

05:16.065 --> 05:18.942
You're as dead as those people...

05:19.110 --> 05:21.111
in the river.

05:21.654 --> 05:22.738
We both are.

05:38.046 --> 05:41.715
Well, slip away

05:46.846 --> 05:53.685
Stuck inside this lonely place

05:53.853 --> 05:57.773
Wonderin' if I'm ever gonna
See your face

05:57.940 --> 06:01.234
It can bring you down

06:01.402 --> 06:07.949
While this world goes round

06:08.117 --> 06:14.331
Time still inside my room

06:14.499 --> 06:19.044
You know it's not too late
Can't be too soon

06:19.212 --> 06:22.714
To be lost and found

06:22.882 --> 06:27.386
To be up and down

06:27.553 --> 06:34.726
And though the world
May close around you

06:34.894 --> 06:37.896
Won't let you slip away

06:38.064 --> 06:42.484
Can't let you slip away from me

07:13.850 --> 07:15.934
Have you decided to take the job?

07:16.102 --> 07:17.936
I saw your ad today.

07:18.104 --> 07:20.105
- I know it's late...
- It's never too late.

07:20.273 --> 07:23.275
After all,
you're about to give me a new life.

07:24.527 --> 07:25.527
Really? When?

07:25.695 --> 07:27.946
When you kill those three bastards.

07:28.114 --> 07:30.282
I'm flattered.

07:30.658 --> 07:33.034
Look, you better get somebody else.

07:33.202 --> 07:35.203
I like your voice.

07:35.371 --> 07:37.914
Yeah, but you don't need
an explosives contractor.

07:38.082 --> 07:40.208
Yes, I do.

07:40.918 --> 07:43.211
- You are my only hope.
- Go to court, use the law.

07:43.379 --> 07:45.505
The law's been bought.

07:46.716 --> 07:49.259
- Then you gotta use a bullet.
- Bullets...

07:49.427 --> 07:50.594
are imprecise.

07:50.761 --> 07:55.098
I heard that you control your explosions,
that you shape your charges.

07:55.266 --> 07:57.726
What I shape and who I shape them for
is my business.

07:57.894 --> 07:59.269
All I'm saying...

07:59.437 --> 08:01.938
word is you were the best.

08:02.106 --> 08:03.356
Whose word?

08:03.524 --> 08:04.983
If we could just meet...

08:05.151 --> 08:08.403
I don't meet, I don't work in Miami
and I don't do jobs like this.

08:08.571 --> 08:11.239
Then why do you keep calling me back?

08:11.407 --> 08:13.116
Why?

08:13.284 --> 08:14.367
I like your voice.

09:01.040 --> 09:03.041
What is it? My cologne?

09:21.644 --> 09:23.144
So, what do you think? You guys coming?

09:23.312 --> 09:24.312
Go ahead, please.

09:24.480 --> 09:25.981
Right.
- How many are there?

09:26.148 --> 09:27.399
Two or eight?

10:20.411 --> 10:23.371
These guys
are killers. You'd be doing the world a favor.

10:23.539 --> 10:27.083
I don't owe the world any favors.
Why did you wait so long?

10:27.251 --> 10:28.293
I thought...

10:29.670 --> 10:32.047
I thought maybe it would pass.

10:32.214 --> 10:34.674
Every day is worse.

10:35.009 --> 10:37.010
Remembering what happened.

10:37.178 --> 10:40.013
That's what I do instead of being alive.

10:40.431 --> 10:43.266
My father hid me in a closet.

10:44.060 --> 10:46.061
I could still see.

10:47.521 --> 10:49.147
My mother suffered.

10:50.149 --> 10:51.816
- No.
- I don't know anything.

10:51.984 --> 10:54.027
They tortured her to get my father to talk.

10:54.195 --> 10:55.570
We're gonna have to kill her.

10:55.988 --> 10:58.448
He walked by something
he shouldn't have seen.

11:00.576 --> 11:03.119
They covered his face
with the pillow from my bed.

11:03.579 --> 11:05.038
- Mommy.
- Waste him.

11:05.623 --> 11:07.040
But it was too small.

11:07.958 --> 11:09.501
So they shot him.

11:11.253 --> 11:14.381
I never thought
blood would be so sticky.

11:15.758 --> 11:18.301
Sometimes I think I can never wash it off.

11:30.106 --> 11:33.650
The only thing I understand
anymore is revenge.

11:33.818 --> 11:36.444
I'm going in and I'm gonna do it myself.

11:36.612 --> 11:39.030
You'll only get one of them.
That's why I need you.

11:41.450 --> 11:42.992
- To do it right.
I told you...

11:43.160 --> 11:45.453
I don't do this kind of job anymore.

12:01.303 --> 12:04.556
I know
you've been watching me, trying to decide...

12:04.724 --> 12:08.643
if I'm on the level,
if you're gonna take the job.

12:08.811 --> 12:10.729
Well, I can't wait anymore, I'm going in.

12:10.896 --> 12:13.648
They'll make you.
I have an alias.

12:13.816 --> 12:15.316
Adrian Hastings.

12:15.484 --> 12:17.318
Wish me luck.

12:50.186 --> 12:51.519
Senor Leon.

12:55.357 --> 12:58.109
So how's it coming in?

12:59.987 --> 13:01.988
Oh, boy. You don't give up. Hmm?

13:03.574 --> 13:07.243
It's packed in Monopoly boxes.

13:07.411 --> 13:09.496
He's right over here.
I want you to meet him.

13:09.663 --> 13:11.498
That's great, Papa.

13:11.665 --> 13:16.377
- You get it in, I'll put it on the street.
- Sure, sure, sure. You do that.

13:18.714 --> 13:20.840
Tomayo, come here.

13:21.008 --> 13:24.135
- Ahem. How you doing, Ned?
- This is a very nice party.

13:24.303 --> 13:27.430
- Yeah.
- You went all out. It's fantastic.

13:30.100 --> 13:33.311
- So let's talk numbers.
- Forget business tonight.

13:33.479 --> 13:36.397
Go grab yourself a nice little mulatta.

13:37.566 --> 13:40.068
I want my money, Tomayo.

13:42.029 --> 13:45.073
An advance.
Small token of my family's goodwill.

13:45.241 --> 13:46.950
Token?

13:47.493 --> 13:49.077
Token.

13:52.414 --> 13:54.457
Now, listen to me, boy.

13:54.625 --> 13:56.084
You know what the Dark Ages are?

13:56.252 --> 13:59.128
The Dark Ages are what I brought
the Leon family out of.

13:59.296 --> 14:00.880
I computerized your operation.

14:01.048 --> 14:05.927
I streamlined your security.
I dragged you into the 20th century.

14:06.428 --> 14:08.638
So don't fuck with me on this.

14:08.806 --> 14:10.139
What is this?

14:10.307 --> 14:13.643
A tip? I don't work for tips.
She works for tips, okay?

14:13.811 --> 14:16.229
Now, I want my money. I want it now.

14:16.397 --> 14:18.314
Go get it.

14:19.358 --> 14:22.485
It's always a pleasure working
with you, Ned.

15:09.533 --> 15:11.200
Champagne, please.

15:34.016 --> 15:35.892
Thank you.

16:15.391 --> 16:17.725
Is there something you want?

16:19.061 --> 16:21.896
What I want, I take.

16:22.064 --> 16:23.439
Champagne?

16:24.149 --> 16:26.192
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

16:29.571 --> 16:31.906
Welcome to our bank.

16:32.908 --> 16:35.410
I've never seen you before.

16:36.036 --> 16:38.121
I used to live here when I was a little girl.

16:39.248 --> 16:41.082
A lot's happened
since you've been gone.

16:41.917 --> 16:43.251
Like what?

16:43.419 --> 16:44.460
Like me.

16:46.171 --> 16:48.715
Insecurity is a terrible thing.

16:48.882 --> 16:50.049
It would be.

16:52.636 --> 16:53.761
I'd like to dance.

16:53.929 --> 16:56.139
What's wrong with keeping
the conversation?

16:56.306 --> 16:59.267
Later. Right now, I'm taking what I want.

17:02.229 --> 17:04.689
You look beautiful tonight.

17:40.893 --> 17:46.731
I'll have my driver to pick you up tomorrow
and I'll show you my Miami.

18:04.291 --> 18:06.250
Now.

18:08.003 --> 18:10.171
Right on time.

18:19.473 --> 18:21.641
Should I do it, Timer?

18:29.483 --> 18:31.359
Morning, sir.

18:33.112 --> 18:34.862
Yeah.

18:40.077 --> 18:41.786
Hey.

18:41.954 --> 18:43.746
- Hey, let him play.
- Hey, baby.

18:43.914 --> 18:45.248
- Come on.
Kind of young...

18:45.415 --> 18:48.042
to be riding this bus alone, aren't you?
Stop it.

18:48.210 --> 18:50.878
- What? Not good enough for you?
Come on, young one.

18:51.046 --> 18:52.713
Don't move over. I wanna play.

18:52.881 --> 18:54.507
Come on, baby.

18:55.884 --> 18:57.176
Come on.
Stop. Leave me alone.

18:57.344 --> 18:58.636
Come on now, what's up, huh?

19:06.979 --> 19:08.813
Come on, baby. Don't be shy.

19:08.981 --> 19:11.357
Here, why don't you take my seat?

19:12.401 --> 19:13.985
Thank you.

19:15.404 --> 19:17.530
Yo, check her out, man.

19:20.617 --> 19:21.659
That seat's taken.

19:21.827 --> 19:24.203
Quit it. Ah!
- Fuck you.

19:25.122 --> 19:27.707
- Excuse me?
- Fuck you.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.417
Come on.

19:29.751 --> 19:30.960
It's all right.

19:34.965 --> 19:37.091
Hold these, please.

19:37.259 --> 19:38.676
Give it back to her.

19:38.844 --> 19:40.469
Stop.

19:46.602 --> 19:47.768
Hey.

19:49.813 --> 19:51.898
What's going on?

19:52.774 --> 19:53.774
You asshole!

19:53.942 --> 19:55.026
Stop that!

20:01.200 --> 20:02.658
You're dead.

20:08.582 --> 20:10.917
I hate knives.

20:16.590 --> 20:19.091
Fuck you, you son of a... Oh!

20:35.817 --> 20:38.236
I believe there's a vacancy.

21:17.651 --> 21:19.610
- So, what do you drink?
- Martini.

21:21.321 --> 21:25.533
Martini on the rocks.
Gold tequila, straight up.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.328
No one knows Miami like I do.

21:31.206 --> 21:33.582
You like spending the day with me?

21:33.750 --> 21:35.126
Yeah.

21:36.586 --> 21:39.005
- Do you?
- Mm-hm.

21:39.172 --> 21:41.841
- Kiss me.
- Hardly know you.

21:47.389 --> 21:50.057
Wait till you try spending the night.

22:00.569 --> 22:02.278
Thanks.

22:20.464 --> 22:22.465
Stay here. I gotta take care of something.

22:23.550 --> 22:25.343
Got a light?

22:32.434 --> 22:34.643
Is this that piece of shit? Hmm?

22:46.656 --> 22:49.033
Where were you?
- I was home.

22:52.871 --> 22:54.121
Thanks.

23:12.641 --> 23:14.642
Thanks, amigo.

23:22.567 --> 23:24.527
What happened to you?

23:24.986 --> 23:28.114
- I just didn't like the show, that's all.
- Uh-huh.

23:28.448 --> 23:30.324
You don't...

23:30.492 --> 23:32.410
walk away from me...

23:33.995 --> 23:35.371
ever.

23:36.164 --> 23:37.706
You understand?

23:38.458 --> 23:39.500
Sorry.

23:41.503 --> 23:43.671
- Get in the car.
- Sure.

24:06.695 --> 24:08.654
Every time...

24:09.322 --> 24:11.574
he touches me, I...

24:13.076 --> 24:16.495
I mean,
he's the man who shot my father.

24:16.663 --> 24:18.205
And he's...

24:20.459 --> 24:23.043
kissing me and...

24:26.756 --> 24:28.716
You don't have to do it.

24:28.884 --> 24:32.720
It's the only way I can get
close enough to kill him.

24:37.058 --> 24:39.894
See, I have this dream.

24:40.061 --> 24:42.980
I'm right there when it happens.

24:43.315 --> 24:47.193
He looks at me like I'm a stranger.

24:47.360 --> 24:49.653
Then I say my name.

24:50.989 --> 24:55.618
And it's the last thing he ever hears.

24:56.328 --> 24:57.661
They don't suspect you?

24:57.829 --> 25:00.789
I'm trusted, for the moment.

25:03.210 --> 25:05.085
He's with you all the time. How do you live?

25:05.253 --> 25:06.795
Alone.

25:07.964 --> 25:09.632
That's not what I mean.

25:10.091 --> 25:12.092
How do you live...

25:12.761 --> 25:13.761
with yourself?

25:13.929 --> 25:15.930
How do you?

26:32.674 --> 26:34.341
Hey, you.

26:36.845 --> 26:38.053
Yeah, I'm talking to you.

26:41.349 --> 26:42.516
You think you know me?

26:43.476 --> 26:46.186
I asked you a question.
You think you know me?

26:47.188 --> 26:50.190
Because the way you're looking at me,
we must be old friends.

26:50.358 --> 26:52.484
Where did we meet?

26:52.652 --> 26:56.030
Nowhere.

26:57.365 --> 26:59.366
You like the bitch? Huh?

27:06.166 --> 27:08.000
Maybe you like me.

27:10.462 --> 27:11.712
No, I don't like you.

27:13.882 --> 27:16.342
Then don't stare so hard.

27:16.509 --> 27:18.969
Somebody could...

27:20.055 --> 27:21.430
put something in your eye.

27:33.818 --> 27:36.403
Fucking pervert.

27:44.913 --> 27:46.789
Let's move it.

28:03.264 --> 28:05.015
Good night.

28:09.729 --> 28:11.438
- Adrian.
- Mm.

29:27.390 --> 29:30.517
- Yeah.
Are you listening?

29:32.520 --> 29:33.729
First rule:

29:34.063 --> 29:36.857
Don't go near them again.

29:37.025 --> 29:38.984
Second rule:

29:39.152 --> 29:40.903
Don't contact me.

29:41.070 --> 29:44.406
- I'll contact you.
- Maybe I can help you.

29:44.574 --> 29:46.784
- Let me see...
- No.

29:46.951 --> 29:49.495
They're my problem now and I'm theirs.

29:53.082 --> 29:55.209
Are you close enough to walk over?

30:03.885 --> 30:05.886
Rule three:

30:06.846 --> 30:08.388
If this is a setup...

30:09.265 --> 30:11.767
I kill you.

30:49.430 --> 30:51.849
- Hey, Manny.
- Now what?

30:52.016 --> 30:54.935
I'm serious. That cop was a regular.
Juanita's moving in on me.

30:55.103 --> 30:58.480
Get the hell out of here.
I don't solve domestic problems.

30:58.648 --> 31:00.357
Asshole.

31:22.964 --> 31:24.923
Don't go anywhere.
I'll be right back.

31:26.301 --> 31:28.468
Lucky me.

32:00.335 --> 32:02.377
Hey, Charlie.

32:18.061 --> 32:20.187
The word is, Manny...

32:20.355 --> 32:21.480
you're skimming.

32:22.523 --> 32:26.693
Somebody's lying.
Hey, hey, I never took a dollar.

32:26.861 --> 32:28.862
I hope it ain't you.

32:29.322 --> 32:32.282
Because if you're trying
to screw Joe Leon...

32:32.450 --> 32:36.703
Charlie, you've known me,
what, 10 years?

32:37.372 --> 32:39.873
- Hey, I'm clean.
- Good.

32:40.249 --> 32:42.209
Very good.

32:42.543 --> 32:45.128
Then you have nothing to worry about,
do you?

32:47.048 --> 32:48.173
Let me see the books.

33:18.621 --> 33:21.415
I can't take this anymore.
That is it. What?

33:21.582 --> 33:24.376
- How about a drink?
- Sure.

33:28.256 --> 33:29.297
September's missing.

33:31.050 --> 33:33.010
See you, Manny.

33:45.314 --> 33:46.732
What do you feel like doing?

33:58.786 --> 34:00.203
What?

34:00.371 --> 34:02.122
I'm working here.

34:02.290 --> 34:03.790
You have two fucking hours.

34:21.641 --> 34:23.143
Get another job, kid.

34:36.032 --> 34:39.493
They got two bodies in there.
Something that used to be Charlie...

34:39.659 --> 34:41.703
and a clean hit
on your brothel manager.

34:41.871 --> 34:42.954
That was a bright move.

34:43.121 --> 34:45.581
Something you ordered
and didn't tell me about?

34:45.750 --> 34:46.792
He was a thief.

34:47.293 --> 34:49.210
- Tell me about the bomb.
Very clean.

34:49.670 --> 34:52.255
There was no damage
to the left or right of the blast.

34:52.422 --> 34:55.509
The item that was used to set it off
was impacted inside the C4...

34:55.676 --> 34:58.553
so the arming device was vaporized.
Brilliant, professional.

34:58.721 --> 35:00.180
Gotta be a specialist.

35:00.556 --> 35:02.682
- This guy is good, Joe.
- Yeah, okay.

35:02.850 --> 35:06.228
He could put a bomb in your crab shell
you wouldn't even know it.

35:07.980 --> 35:09.314
I'll kill the son of a bitch.

35:09.482 --> 35:13.068
You can't kill anybody,
Tomayo, until we know who he is, can you?

35:14.237 --> 35:15.570
I'll find him.

35:15.738 --> 35:18.573
The important thing to find out,
who he works for.

35:19.408 --> 35:20.700
Maybe he works for the CIA.

35:20.868 --> 35:23.537
Maybe he works for the Mafia,
the Italians, I don't know...

35:23.704 --> 35:26.039
but we have to find out who, okay?

35:26.207 --> 35:27.207
Overview, Joe.

35:28.042 --> 35:31.002
We have to ask ourselves
what does eliminating Charlie mean...

35:31.170 --> 35:32.879
in the overall picture?
- Nothing.

35:33.047 --> 35:35.465
Less than nothing.
So this target wasn't territorial.

35:35.883 --> 35:36.925
It was personal.

35:38.302 --> 35:40.345
How the fuck do you know so much?

35:40.513 --> 35:44.224
He's guessing, Pop. Let me take a couple
of the boys, I'll find out who this is.

35:44.392 --> 35:47.435
Wait a minute. Give me a second here.
I have to make a decision.

35:49.230 --> 35:52.107
Little time to think here, huh?

35:55.069 --> 35:57.112
Okay.

35:57.280 --> 35:58.530
You take over, okay?

35:59.448 --> 36:03.118
- Papa...
- I said, Trent will handle it, okay?

36:03.286 --> 36:05.495
- I don't hear you saying "okay. "
- Okay, Papa.

36:05.663 --> 36:07.080
- What did you say?
- Okay, Papa.

36:07.248 --> 36:09.249
That's nice. Thank you.

36:16.132 --> 36:18.842
I'm gonna need resources
on this one, Joe.

36:19.010 --> 36:21.595
And also, the place was crawling
with cops.

36:21.762 --> 36:24.848
I can't be tripping over fucking
civil servants every move I make.

36:25.016 --> 36:28.602
- I need total control.
- Yeah, okay, well, I will...

36:28.769 --> 36:31.646
I will take care of that, you know?

36:34.942 --> 36:38.028
Personally. Okay?

38:00.111 --> 38:02.070
Hello, Timer.

38:02.655 --> 38:04.823
Having a good day?

38:09.912 --> 38:13.331
Here you go. Knock yourself out.

38:47.450 --> 38:49.576
I saw it on the news.

38:50.036 --> 38:52.245
You got the first one.

38:52.413 --> 38:53.663
Thank you.

38:54.290 --> 38:57.751
- Thank you.
Well, I'm just doing my job.

38:57.918 --> 39:00.628
- You gotta stay away from the other two.
I could help you.

39:00.796 --> 39:03.006
I could set them up for you.

39:03.174 --> 39:06.176
No, no.
You just stay away from those guys.

39:06.719 --> 39:09.804
Their future is about to become very dark.

39:09.972 --> 39:14.434
You're still following me. Aren't you?

39:15.936 --> 39:18.688
- It's gotten so I can feel you.
It's all part of the work.

39:20.066 --> 39:21.608
Do you think about me?

39:21.776 --> 39:23.902
I think about you.

39:24.070 --> 39:26.154
My own personal ghost.

39:27.239 --> 39:28.365
Or angel maybe.

39:29.617 --> 39:32.077
- We could meet.
You are a beautiful woman.

39:32.787 --> 39:33.953
But I don't meet.

39:34.121 --> 39:37.957
- When this is over, I should leave.
When are you gonna do it?

39:38.751 --> 39:39.959
Soon.

39:40.127 --> 39:42.212
Very soon.

39:48.302 --> 39:50.261
Trent, you know the chief of police.

39:50.429 --> 39:52.764
Trent is gonna work with us
on this problem.

39:52.932 --> 39:57.310
You know,
I mean, he was a former employee of the...

39:57.478 --> 39:58.978
CIA.

